{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Embedding vector dimensionality matches the vector DB index dimension for a given query.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"A mock embedding client can easily return the expected shape and miss real failures like model-version drift (e.g., 1536 vs 3072 dims) or runtime contract mismatches with the actual embedding provider/index metadata. Catching this reliably requires calling the real embedding endpoint and validating against the real index dimension.","test_description":"Run an API-level test against a real embedding service and real vector index metadata: submit a query, capture produced embedding length, fetch index dimension, and assert exact equality. Fail if provider/model config changes and dimensions diverge.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Similarity search returns results in descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pure mocks can hide ranking/sorting bugs and metric misconfiguration. This is best validated with real search components wired together (embedding/vector query/scoring path) against seeded data, but does not require external network APIs if run on a local DB/test index.","test_description":"Seed a local test vector index with controlled vectors and known cosine relationships. Execute similarity search through the real repository/service stack and assert returned scores are monotonically non-increasing and IDs match expected rank order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"LLM re-ranking changes ordering for nuanced-intent queries versus raw similarity ranking.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior depends on semantic judgment from a real LLM; mocked outputs can trivially satisfy the condition and miss real failures where reranking does not meaningfully respond to nuance. Outcome can vary across runs/model updates, so real model behavior is part of the failure boundary.","test_description":"Use a fixed nuanced query plus a candidate set where lexical similarity and contextual intent differ. Run raw similarity ranking, then call the real LLM reranker and assert order differs in at least one meaningful position (with repetition/tolerance to account for model variance).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Queries with no close matches return an empty set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A mock can force empty output and miss real thresholding failures (distance cutoff not applied, score normalization bugs, default top-K leakage). Needs real retrieval logic plus threshold policy over a controlled dataset; no real LLM quality dependence is required.","test_description":"Create a local index where all items are intentionally far from the test query. Execute full retrieval (pre-rerank and rerank path if applicable) and assert final results are empty when all scores are below the configured relevance threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Median end-to-end latency (query receipt to reranked response) remains below 2 seconds.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Latency is dominated by real infrastructure effects (network, provider latency, serialization, queueing, DB/service behavior). In-process mocks will systematically under-report and can hide production regressions. Requires real end-to-end execution.","test_description":"Run a system performance test against deployed/staging services with production-like dependencies. Execute a representative query set, record end-to-end response times, compute median (p50), and assert p50 < 2000 ms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
